In Levitivus after the De grees of bloud, in which wee are for
bidden to marrie, the Lorde doeth pre
sently adde: In all these be not ye de
filed: For in all those thinges are the
nations defiled, which I cast out be
fore you. And hereby the lande is de
filed, and I have visited the iniquitie
thereof uppon it, and the lande hath
spewed out the inhabitauntes thereof.
Yee shall therefore keepe my statutes
and mine ordinances, and shall not
doe anie of all these abhominations.
For whosoever shall doe so, he shall be
cut off from among his pleople. And
in the 20. Chapter of Leviticus, hee
hath appointed death to be the punish
ment of Incest, which is not changed
by the civill lawes, or Imperiall con
stitutions.
The abhominable sinne of Sodomie
and medling with beasts also is plain
ly forbitden. Against which we have
most evident and expresse Lawes set
downe in the I S. and 20. chapter of Le
viticus. We have also a very severe,
but yet a most just punishment layd by
God himselfe upon the pates of the de
testable Sodomites. For with fire and
stinking brimstone sent down fro hea
ven, he consumed those filthie men to
dust and ashes, which ashes be washed
away with the waves of the dead sea,
because he would not have so much as
the very cinders to remaine of so wic
ked men.
Moreover their whole cities & fruit
full fieldes were burnt with fire. For
it was not requisite that one jot of the
substance of those most wicked men
should remaine undestroyed.
The place where those Cities some
time were situated, is at this day over
flowen with water, & called the dead
Sea. Whereby we doe consequent
ly gather, that the most just God will
